rules:
- id: rule-promotion-requires-evidence
  precedence: global
  scope: global
  summary: Pattern promotion to core must be supported by strong evidence, preferably
    from multiple sources or systems.
  title: Rule Promotion Requires Evidence
- id: rule-shared-knowledge-workspace
  precedence: global
  scope: global
  summary: Projects must participate in a shared Knowledge Workspace and avoid duplicating
    existing workspace-level governance structures.
  title: Rule Shared Knowledge Workspace
- id: rule-decisions-must-be-persisted
  precedence: global
  scope: global
  summary: All architectural decisions must be persisted as structured decision records
    (ADR) before being reflected in other artifacts.
  title: Rule Decisions Must Be Persisted
- id: rule-decision-schema-must-be-structured
  precedence: global
  scope: global
  summary: All decisions must be expressed using a structured YAML decision schema
    rather than unstructured narrative text.
  title: Rule Decision Schema Must Be Structured
- id: rule-pattern-decision-lifecycle-alignment
  precedence: global
  scope: global
  summary: Ensures consistent interpretation between pattern maturity and decision
    lifecycle without conflating knowledge evolution with governance status.
  title: Rule Pattern Decision Lifecycle Alignment
- id: rule-do-not-merge-across-architectural-layers
  precedence: global
  scope: global
  summary: Patterns must not be merged or consolidated across different architectural
    layers to preserve clarity and separation of concerns.
  title: Rule Do Not Merge Across Architectural Layers
- id: rule-decision-status-drives-stage
  precedence: global
  scope: global
  summary: The lifecycle stage of any architecture item must be derived from its decision
    status; items not 'accepted' cannot be marked as DONE.
  title: Rule Decision Status Drives Stage
- id: rule-language-semantic-contract
  precedence: global
  scope: global
  summary: Defines the semantic contract for language used in architecture artefacts
    to ensure clarity, consistency, and alignment.
  title: Rule Language Semantic Contract
- id: rule-signal-promotion-criteria
  precedence: global
  scope: global
  summary: Defines mandatory criteria (recurrence, impact, reusability, stability)
    and evidence requirements for promoting signals to patterns.
  title: Rule Signal Promotion Criteria
- id: rule-patterns-born-as-supporting
  precedence: global
  scope: global
  summary: All patterns must be created as supporting by default and never directly
    as core to ensure validation through usage.
  title: Rule Patterns Born As Supporting
- id: rule-aem-consistency-with-decisions
  precedence: global
  scope: global
  summary: Ensures the Architecture Evolution Map (AEM) reflects and does not contradict
    Architecture Decision Records (ADR).
  title: Rule Aem Consistency With Decisions
- id: rule-architecture-work-authority
  precedence: global
  scope: global
  summary: Architecture Work is the authoritative source for planning state; generated
    artifacts must derive status from this source.
  title: Rule Architecture Work Authority
- id: rule-adr-single-source-of-truth
  precedence: global
  scope: global
  summary: Architecture decisions must be recorded and updated only in ADRs; all other
    representations must be derived from them.
  title: Rule Adr Single Source Of Truth
- id: rule-generated-artifacts-not-authoritative
  precedence: global
  scope: global
  summary: Generated governance artifacts must summarize authoritative sources and
    must not become the authoritative source themselves.
  title: Rule Generated Artifacts Not Authoritative
- id: rule-precedence-hierarchy
  precedence: global
  scope: global
  summary: Defines the precedence model (Global > Project > Prompt) for resolving
    conflicts between rules from different sources.
  title: Rule Precedence Hierarchy
- id: rule-system-proposes-architect-decides
  precedence: global
  scope: global
  summary: All architectural decisions must be proposed by the system and explicitly
    accepted, rejected, or deferred by an architect.
  title: Rule System Proposes Architect Decides
- id: rule-core-patterns-must-be-foundational
  precedence: global
  scope: global
  summary: Core patterns must represent foundational architectural primitives rather
    than specific strategies or implementations.
  title: Rule Core Patterns Must Be Foundational
- id: rule-heuristic-patterns-require-signals
  precedence: global
  scope: global
  summary: All heuristic-derived patterns must include at least one linked signal
    as evidence to ensure grounding in observed behavior.
  title: Rule Heuristic Patterns Require Signals
summary:
  global_rules: 18
  project_rules: 0
  total_rules: 18
